Hey. Hi.

4
00:00:09,940 --> 00:00:12,679
Look, first thing, I love you.

5
00:00:12,747 --> 00:00:14,566
Well, that's good.

6
00:00:14,651 --> 00:00:15,999
But this is going to be the third
time this week that I do this.

7
00:00:16,066 --> 00:00:17,888
No! I know, I'm sorry.

8
00:00:17,955 --> 00:00:19,096
But half the staff's got the flu,

9
00:00:19,163 --> 00:00:20,700
Half's got some sort of respiratory virus.

10
00:00:20,768 --> 00:00:21,700
I just can't get out of here.

11
00:00:21,768 --> 00:00:22,705
Not even for lunch?

12
00:00:22,773 --> 00:00:23,907
We can go to the cafeteria.

13
00:00:23,974 --> 00:00:24,906
But I gotta work a double.

14
00:00:24,974 --> 00:00:26,141
Is this even safe?

15
00:00:26,209 --> 00:00:27,644
I mean, I don't understand

16
00:00:27,711 --> 00:00:29,211
The medical profession,
and I feel like doctors

17
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:30,579
And truck drivers-- truck drivers?

18
00:00:30,646 --> 00:00:32,412
And pilots, you know,
they should get the most sleep,

19
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:33,844
You know, not the least.

20
00:00:35,912 --> 00:00:38,680
Well, we got vegetarian lasagna today, ehhh.

21
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,682
Help.

22
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,184
Somebody help me.

23
00:00:42,252 --> 00:00:43,653
Hey, what's the problem?

24
00:00:43,721 --> 00:00:45,387
Sir, did something happen to you?

25
00:00:45,455 --> 00:00:46,787
He had a knife.
Why aren't you listening to me?

26
00:00:46,855 --> 00:00:48,887
Lock the door. Lock the door.
Just lock the door.

27
00:00:48,955 --> 00:00:50,255
Call the police.
You should definitely do that.

28
00:00:52,224 --> 00:00:53,324
Sir, we need to examine you.

29
00:00:53,392 --> 00:00:54,526
Yeah, let's do that right now.

30
00:00:54,594 --> 00:00:56,027
Ok, why don't we examine you.

31
00:00:56,095 --> 00:00:57,195
Just sit down. Help me get him to a chair.

32
00:00:57,263 --> 00:00:58,496
He had a knife. He had a knife. Whoa!

33
00:00:58,564 --> 00:00:59,497
He won't stop slashing!

34
00:00:59,565 --> 00:01:01,098
He just kept slashing!

35
00:01:03,902 --> 00:01:05,771
Let go of her. He won't stop slashing!

36
00:01:05,838 --> 00:01:07,069
He just kept slashing.
Can we get security down here?

37
00:01:07,136 --> 00:01:08,834
His eyes, his eyes!

38
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:10,369
Are you gonna be all right?

39
00:01:10,437 --> 00:01:11,704
It's going to be fine, sir. Calm down.

40
00:01:11,772 --> 00:01:12,705
Where is security? And the blood!

41
00:01:12,773 --> 00:01:14,174
And the blood, you have to stop him!

42
00:01:14,242 --> 00:01:16,976
There was an officer in peed's
talking with a social worker.

43
00:01:17,044 --> 00:01:19,078
Call over there.
Just get someone who is armed.

44
00:01:19,145 --> 00:01:20,312
Won't do any good.

45
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:22,080
They can't stop it.

46
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:24,114
Stop it? Do you know what happened to him?

47
00:01:24,182 --> 00:01:26,149
They can't save him no matter what they do.

48
00:01:26,217 --> 00:01:28,384
He's a dead man.

49
00:01:33,122 --> 00:01:35,156
Child, whispering: Can you see us?

50
00:01:35,223 --> 00:01:45,225
Sync by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com

51
00:02:09,594 --> 00:02:10,561
Hey. Why aren't you listening to me?!

52
00:02:10,628 --> 00:02:11,761
Please, someone just listen to me!

53
00:02:11,828 --> 00:02:12,862
How is he? I don't know.

54
00:02:12,929 --> 00:02:14,530
The er doctor took over.

55
00:02:14,597 --> 00:02:15,798
They want to sedate him,
but they say he's got to talk to police.

56
00:02:15,865 --> 00:02:17,132
Ok, well, you should talk to him first,

57
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,199
Or get me in there.

58
00:02:18,267 --> 00:02:19,434
Wait, did you see something?

59
00:02:19,501 --> 00:02:22,069
Something and someone. I had a vision.

60
00:02:22,137 --> 00:02:23,337
I saw someone with a knife.

61
00:02:23,404 --> 00:02:24,704
Just like he said.

62
00:02:24,772 --> 00:02:26,839
Except it was a woman.
She was screaming and bleeding.

63
00:02:26,907 --> 00:02:28,874
Do you think someone else was attacked?

64
00:02:28,942 --> 00:02:30,275
Did he say anything about a woman?

65
00:02:30,343 --> 00:02:32,144
No, but, I mean, he's in shock.

66
00:02:32,211 --> 00:02:34,379
Oh, boy. Right this way, officers.

67
00:02:34,447 --> 00:02:35,847
He said someone is after him.
The patient's this way.

68
00:02:35,914 --> 00:02:37,214
Did you see the person holding the knife?

69
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,782
I think it was a man.

70
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:39,883
Do you think you could describe

71
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:41,084
The woman in the vision to the police?

72
00:02:41,151 --> 00:02:43,152
Dirty blond hair,
an intense cut on her forearm.

73
00:02:43,220 --> 00:02:44,286
I don't even know if she's still alive.

74
00:02:44,354 --> 00:02:45,521
All right, that's the something you saw.

75
00:02:45,588 --> 00:02:47,188
What about the someone? Ghost.

76
00:02:47,256 --> 00:02:48,790
In his thirties.
It was kind of hard to make out.

77
00:02:48,857 --> 00:02:50,258
But he wasn't cut, he wasn't bleeding,

78
00:02:50,326 --> 00:02:51,293
He just looked awful.

79
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,660
What is he, a third victim?

80
00:02:52,728 --> 00:02:54,428
Or the attacker.
Maybe someone that the guy--

81
00:02:54,496 --> 00:02:55,862
Robert, his name's robert.

82
00:02:55,930 --> 00:02:58,031
Ok, maybe somebody that
robert killed in a struggle.

83
00:02:58,099 --> 00:02:59,432
Wait, he didn't even know it?

84
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,034
I mean, like, he was being
chased and didn't know?

85
00:03:01,101 --> 00:03:03,069
All I know is that the ghost said
there's nothing anyone could do.

86
00:03:03,137 --> 00:03:05,671
And that your patient
robert is going to die.

87
00:03:06,973 --> 00:03:08,040
Is he?

88
00:03:08,107 --> 00:03:09,241
I don't know. It's tough to tell.

89
00:03:09,308 --> 00:03:10,575
With a knife wound,

90
00:03:10,643 --> 00:03:12,377
Sometimes you gotta open
them up and see the damage.

91
00:03:12,445 --> 00:03:13,611
Ok, well, you need to get to him
before he gets into surgery.

92
00:03:13,679 --> 00:03:15,180
That woman could still be out there.

93
00:03:15,247 --> 00:03:16,848
Yeah, and she might still
be alive, right? Ok.

94
00:03:26,887 --> 00:03:29,388
So he's stable. I'll notify the e.R.

95
00:03:29,456 --> 00:03:32,656
Good. I'll be back, dr. Myers.

96
00:03:32,724 --> 00:03:35,024
Hey, wesley.

97
00:03:35,092 --> 00:03:36,192
What's going on in there?

98
00:03:36,259 --> 00:03:37,893
Dr. Meyers is just finishing up the exam.

99
00:03:37,961 --> 00:03:38,928
He's gonna be fine.

100
00:03:38,996 --> 00:03:40,729
They're not going to open him up?

101
00:03:40,797 --> 00:03:41,730
No, we checked him out.

102
00:03:41,798 --> 00:03:42,931
He's got lots of abrasions

103
00:03:42,999 --> 00:03:44,632
And some moderate lacerations.

104
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:46,400
Nothing that looks like a knife wound.

105
00:03:46,468 --> 00:03:47,635
What about all that blood he came in with?

106
00:03:47,702 --> 00:03:50,004
Well, like I said, he's pretty banged up.

107
00:03:50,071 --> 00:03:52,005
Anybody know why?

108
00:03:52,073 --> 00:03:54,341
He keeps talking about
some guy with a knife.

109
00:03:54,409 --> 00:03:57,777
Maybe he got knocked around
pretty good trying to get away.

110
00:03:57,845 --> 00:03:59,779
I really need to talk to him.

111
00:03:59,847 --> 00:04:02,948
Those cops are waiting to
talk to him, too, you know.

112
00:04:03,016 --> 00:04:05,884
Yeah.

113
00:04:07,152 --> 00:04:08,719
I need to talk to him first,

114
00:04:08,787 --> 00:04:12,088
So could you hold them
off for about 5 minutes?

115
00:04:12,156 --> 00:04:13,389
You got it. Thanks.

116
00:04:19,729 --> 00:04:22,396
Hey, mr. Wharton, how are you doing?

117
00:04:23,699 --> 00:04:25,900
Who are you?

118
00:04:25,967 --> 00:04:27,902
I'm a doctor. Well, actually I'm the guy

119
00:04:27,969 --> 00:04:29,603
Who threw you in the wheelchair
when you first came in here.

120
00:04:29,671 --> 00:04:31,471
Oh, I'm sorry.

121
00:04:31,539 --> 00:04:33,873
It's just, I'm so tired.

122
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,974
It's probably the adrenaline.
You know, it spikes

123
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:37,942
And then your body crashes.

124
00:04:38,009 --> 00:04:39,576
They said there's nothing wrong with me.

125
00:04:39,644 --> 00:04:41,277
No, not too much. Nothing serious.

126
00:04:41,345 --> 00:04:46,015
Look, this attack you've
been talking about...

127
00:04:46,082 --> 00:04:47,516
Was there anyone else who got hurt?

128
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:48,717
Anyone else?

129
00:04:48,784 --> 00:04:49,717
Someone who was with you.

130
00:04:49,785 --> 00:04:51,685
You know, a woman, maybe?

131
00:04:51,753 --> 00:04:53,720
Ah, I don't know.

132
00:04:53,788 --> 00:04:54,821
All right.

133
00:04:54,889 --> 00:04:56,389
Mr. Wharton?

134
00:04:58,025 --> 00:05:00,192
Do you mind if I call you robert?

135
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:01,627
Look, robert,

136
00:05:01,694 --> 00:05:04,562
Someone saw a woman being
attacked with a knife.

137
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:05,897
Where?

138
00:05:05,965 --> 00:05:07,198
Well, that's what I was
hoping you could tell me.

139
00:05:07,266 --> 00:05:11,202
You came in here,
you haven't been cut by a knife,

140
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:13,303
But it turns out this woman was.

141
00:05:13,371 --> 00:05:15,939
It wasn't a dream.

142
00:05:16,007 --> 00:05:18,641
Wait, you know what I'm talking about?

143
00:05:18,709 --> 00:05:20,776
This actually happened?

144
00:05:20,844 --> 00:05:23,378
Robert... Who was she?

145
00:05:23,446 --> 00:05:26,380
Who was she?

146
00:05:26,447 --> 00:05:28,248
Can you tell me anything about this attack?

147
00:05:28,315 --> 00:05:29,581
Look, where did it happen? Were you inside?

148
00:05:29,649 --> 00:05:31,617
Were you outside, were you in a building?

149
00:05:31,684 --> 00:05:33,285
Tell me any sounds you heard, anything.

150
00:05:33,353 --> 00:05:36,388
The night was just so dark.

151
00:05:36,456 --> 00:05:39,291
I just wanted to shut my eyes.

152
00:05:39,358 --> 00:05:42,493
I thought, please,
could I just shut my eyes?

153
00:05:42,561 --> 00:05:44,328
Hey, man, it's the middle of the afternoon.

154
00:05:44,396 --> 00:05:46,063
This went on all night?

155
00:05:46,131 --> 00:05:47,331
I don't know.

156
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:48,432
Who did this to you?

157
00:05:48,499 --> 00:05:50,066
What the hell happened to you?

158
00:05:50,134 --> 00:05:52,834
Robert, where were you before you came here?

159
00:05:54,036 --> 00:05:55,770
Where am I now?

160
00:05:55,837 --> 00:05:57,838
You're in the rockland memorial hospital.

161
00:05:57,905 --> 00:05:59,406
Who are you?

162
00:05:59,473 --> 00:06:00,773
My name's jim, I'm a doctor.

163
00:06:00,841 --> 00:06:02,641
You don't remember coming here, do you?

164
00:06:04,444 --> 00:06:05,477
I wake up in places,

165
00:06:05,544 --> 00:06:07,579
And I can't remember how I got there.

166
00:06:07,646 --> 00:06:09,948
Was I sleeping?

167
00:06:10,016 --> 00:06:13,318
Just now, was I sleeping?

168
00:06:13,386 --> 00:06:15,153
No, it's like you're blacking out.

169
00:06:15,221 --> 00:06:16,521
Yeah.

170
00:06:16,589 --> 00:06:19,290
I guess so.

171
00:06:19,358 --> 00:06:22,593
I think so.

172
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:25,762
Robert, I'm going to ask you a
very important question, all right?

173
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:28,664
You came in here covered with blood.

174
00:06:28,732 --> 00:06:30,166
Was that blood yours?

175
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:32,034
I don't know.

176
00:06:32,102 --> 00:06:34,669
Robert, tell me. Did you hurt somebody?

177
00:06:34,737 --> 00:06:36,004
Somebody you knew, anybody?

178
00:06:36,071 --> 00:06:37,238
A woman? Did you?

179
00:06:37,306 --> 00:06:39,974
No, no, I wouldn't. I couldn't.

180
00:06:40,042 --> 00:06:43,210
I hope not.

181
00:06:45,179 --> 00:06:48,014
Am I awake?

182
00:06:48,082 --> 00:06:49,715
I mean, is this place real?

183
00:06:51,551 --> 00:06:54,419
Are you real?

184
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:02,858
You see?

185
00:07:05,728 --> 00:07:07,462
It's in him now.

186
00:07:07,529 --> 00:07:10,364
It's in him now?

187
00:07:10,432 --> 00:07:11,364
What does that mean?

188
00:07:11,432 --> 00:07:12,798
Melinda wasn't exactly sure,

189
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,166
And the ghost didn't
stick around to explain.

190
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:15,233
Where is she?

191
00:07:15,301 --> 00:07:16,835
She's giving eli the local ghost update.

192
00:07:16,902 --> 00:07:18,336
What do I do?

193
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:20,206
I want you to find out everything
you can about robert wharton.

194
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:22,676
You mean, about people he knows who died.

195
00:07:22,744 --> 00:07:24,844
Yeah, but especially the one we hope didn't.

196
00:07:24,912 --> 00:07:26,145
The woman that she saw getting cut.

197
00:07:26,213 --> 00:07:27,947
Yeah. So look at his friends, ok?

198
00:07:28,015 --> 00:07:29,149
But don't rule anybody out.

199
00:07:29,217 --> 00:07:30,884
And see if anybody's gone
missing in grandview.

200
00:07:30,952 --> 00:07:33,320
If not, nearby towns, ok? I'm on it.

201
00:07:33,388 --> 00:07:34,521
Thanks, man.

202
00:07:34,589 --> 00:07:36,756
Hey, so is detective blair.

203
00:07:36,824 --> 00:07:38,524
She must have gotten melinda's message.

204
00:07:38,592 --> 00:07:39,858
All right, you hear anything, call me.

205
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:40,859
Ok.

206
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:43,328
Thanks, man. Take it easy.

207
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:47,765
So you're sure that this is the man you saw?

208
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,333
Yeah. That's the guy

209
00:07:49,401 --> 00:07:51,235
I saw sleeping on the bench.

210
00:07:51,303 --> 00:07:53,770
And you didn't see anyone with him,

211
00:07:53,838 --> 00:07:55,205
Near him, menacing him?

212
00:07:55,272 --> 00:07:57,974
No. But as he was curling up to go to sleep,

213
00:07:58,041 --> 00:08:00,175
I noticed he might be hurt.

214
00:08:00,243 --> 00:08:01,677
So I asked him if he was ok,

215
00:08:01,744 --> 00:08:04,779
And he looked at me like totally lost.

216
00:08:04,847 --> 00:08:06,414
And I pointed out the blood.

217
00:08:06,482 --> 00:08:08,949
That's when he ran away.

218
00:08:09,017 --> 00:08:10,417
When he realized you saw the blood.

219
00:08:10,485 --> 00:08:11,585
Yeah.

220
00:08:11,653 --> 00:08:14,121
Excuse me. Sorry, detective blair.

221
00:08:14,188 --> 00:08:15,688
But I was here when the guy

222
00:08:15,756 --> 00:08:17,123
You're talking about was brought in,

223
00:08:17,191 --> 00:08:19,158
And he told us he was being chased.

224
00:08:19,226 --> 00:08:21,860
Yeah, by someone with a knife.

225
00:08:21,927 --> 00:08:24,128
I didn't see anyone.

226
00:08:24,196 --> 00:08:27,498
And I'm telling you, the person
he was running from was me.

227
00:08:27,565 --> 00:08:28,565
And then what happened?

228
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,400
I followed him. I lost him

229
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:32,368
For a few minutes, but then I saw him

230
00:08:32,436 --> 00:08:34,937
Ducking into the hospital, and...

231
00:08:35,005 --> 00:08:38,607
Here I am.

232
00:08:40,242 --> 00:08:41,543
This guy walks into a hospital

233
00:08:41,610 --> 00:08:42,577
Screaming he's been attacked

234
00:08:42,644 --> 00:08:43,911
When he's the attacker?

235
00:08:43,979 --> 00:08:45,980
It's a possibility, that's all I'm saying.

236
00:08:46,047 --> 00:08:48,348
I've heard about throwing
suspicion onto someone else,

237
00:08:48,416 --> 00:08:50,250
But come on, be smart.

238
00:08:50,317 --> 00:08:53,852
Only do it after the police are onto you.

239
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:57,322
Or this guy robert could have had
some kind of psychotic break.

240
00:08:57,390 --> 00:08:59,457
Yeah, and really believes
everything he's saying.

241
00:08:59,525 --> 00:09:00,858
I really don't think he
has any idea what he did.

242
00:09:00,926 --> 00:09:03,260
And, you know, we have no
idea what he's capable of.

243
00:09:03,328 --> 00:09:04,495
All right, well, can you check his records?

244
00:09:04,562 --> 00:09:06,630
Find out if he's under psychiatric care?

245
00:09:06,697 --> 00:09:07,864
Maybe he went off his meds.

246
00:09:07,932 --> 00:09:09,832
He had nothing on him. No wallet, nothing.

247
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,534
Only information we have is
his name and his blood type.

248
00:09:11,601 --> 00:09:13,702
And the blood that was on his shirt,
they're testing it,

249
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:15,437
So if there was a second type...

250
00:09:15,505 --> 00:09:17,172
Then he might have hurt someone else.

251
00:09:17,239 --> 00:09:18,940
The woman you saw. Or the ghost, right?

252
00:09:19,007 --> 00:09:22,076
I mean, there is one dead
person in this scenario?

253
00:09:22,143 --> 00:09:23,810
The ghost said you can't save him.

254
00:09:23,878 --> 00:09:26,346
Maybe he meant robert
should fry for what he did.

255
00:09:26,414 --> 00:09:29,582
But even if he killed both of them,
that's unlikely.

256
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:32,051
So...Look, I'm not sure.

257
00:09:32,118 --> 00:09:34,586
But I don't think this
guy meant to hurt anyone.

258
00:09:34,654 --> 00:09:36,521
I mean, he seems like he wants to help.

259
00:09:36,589 --> 00:09:37,855
Good.

260
00:09:37,923 --> 00:09:40,224
'cause I want to talk to him.

261
00:09:40,292 --> 00:09:42,426
We sent officers over to
robert's place of employment

